Vol / Page: 244
Edition: 1961
Quote:  The boys preparing a <i>Wata</i>, a high stand for [245] native food, about 16ft. long and 10 wide, 16ft from the ground, to preserve it from the English rats which are now beginning to infest all parts of the land ...
