Author: POLACK
Vol / Page: 1/65
Edition:
Quote: The many <i> watas </i> [a's-acute], or platforms raised on trees, to protect the provisions of the people from the rapacity of the dogs and rats, were loaded with seed potatoes, ready for planting. <i>Ibid.</i> 1/167 ... he accordingly mounted a wata [a's-acute], where the provisions are always kept, and brought down a small flax basket, containing the human viand. </i>Ibid.</i>2/27 Platforms (watas[a2-acute] ...  <i>Ibid.</i> 2/33 The watta [as-acute] is a platform built upon trees, or raised on stout branches. These are solely used for the purpose of preserving the provisions ...
