Date: 0/0/1898
Source: Austral English
Author: MORRIS
Vol / Page: 508
Edition:
Quote: <i> Whata, n.</i> Maori word for a storehouse on posts or other supports, like a <i> Pataka </i> (q.v.). <i>Futtah </i> (q.v.) is a corruption, probably of Irish origin.
Notes:

