Date: 0/0/1945
Source: Maori Place-Names of Canterbury
Author: BEATTIE
Vol / Page: 33
Edition:
Quote: Besides the whare (houses), there were whata (futtahs) standing there when I was a boy. They stood on two posts, and each post had a niche cut round it to stop the rats from getting up to the food stored on them. There was no roof on them, the food being covered with flax mats.
Notes:

